  "texts": [
    "Then, the node only keeps the 𝑚 closest neighbors, where 𝑚 is a user-parameter.",
    "The pre-existing graph could be a random graph or some other type of graph.",
    "Incremental Insertion (II) refers to building a graph by inserting one vertex at a time.",
    "Each vertex is connected using bi-directional edges to its nearest neighbors and some distant vertices.",
    "The neighbors are selected using a beam search on the already inserted portion of the graph."
  ],
